            <p>A dead pixel is a single point on your screen that no longer produces light or color. Because its transistor has stopped receiving power, it stays permanently black regardless of what the display is showing. On an LCD or OLED panel, a dead pixel appears as a tiny dark dot that never changes, which makes it easiest to spot against a pure white background during a screen dead pixel test.</p>
